{"title":"Must Watch: Get amped for Red Bull Rampage by dropping off a 4-story building","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/14/must-watch-get-amped-for-red-bull-rampage-by-dropping-off-a-4-story-building/","date":1634207720000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14054127/Red-Bull-Rampage-for-Scale_photo-by-William-Saunders_Jaxson-Riddle-jumps-off-a-4-story-building-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Getting a sense of scale for the Red Bull Rampage, photo by William Saunders, Jaxson Riddle rides off a 4-story building\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14054127/Red-Bull-Rampage-for-Scale_photo-by-William-Saunders_Jaxson-Riddle-jumps-off-a-4-story-building-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14054127/Red-Bull-Rampage-for-Scale_photo-by-William-Saunders_Jaxson-Riddle-jumps-off-a-4-story-building-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14054127/Red-Bull-Rampage-for-Scale_photo-by-William-Saunders_Jaxson-Riddle-jumps-off-a-4-story-building-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14054127/Red-Bull-Rampage-for-Scale_photo-by-William-Saunders_Jaxson-Riddle-jumps-off-a-4-story-building-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14054127/Red-Bull-Rampage-for-Scale_photo-by-William-Saunders_Jaxson-Riddle-jumps-off-a-4-story-building-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14054127/Red-Bull-Rampage-for-Scale_photo-by-William-Saunders_Jaxson-Riddle-jumps-off-a-4-story-building.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-274801\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>There’s no denying that Red Bull Rampage is a spectacle of extreme mountain biking that we can’t take our eyes off. But it’s hard to really grasp the scale of 70′ drops, 75′ gap jumps &amp; 85° lead-in ramps out in the vast scale of desert cliffs – all with crazy flips &amp; tricks thrown in too. So with this year’s Rampagers out in Virgin, Utah dialing in lines as we speak, and the 2021 Red Bull Rampage set to kick off tomorrow, Red Bull decided to jump off a 4-story building back in town to give us a little more context.</p><p>You do kinda have to see it to believe it…</p><h2>Get a sense of scale of Red Bull Rampage!</h2><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ZLqSeKKHi_w?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></p><p>Red Bull enlisted Nicholi Rogatkin, who famously had one of the <a href=\"https://www.redbull.com/us-en/rampage-2015-nicholi-rogatkin\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">biggest-ever Rampage crashes</a> and then finished his run (with another giant canyon gap &amp; a backflip – seriously, click that link and go watch it again!), and Jaxson Riddle, a young freerider born just 30 miles away the year the first Rampage was run, to help us get a sense of Rampage’s scale.</p><p>The jumps are huge, the gaps seem even more massive when you put one on a flat parking lot with a couple of trucks in the middle.</p><div id=\"attachment_274812\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14054122/Red-Bull-Rampage-for-Scale_photo-by-William-Saunders_Jaxson-Riddle-dropping-in.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-274812\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14054122/Red-Bull-Rampage-for-Scale_photo-by-William-Saunders_Jaxson-Riddle-dropping-in.jpg\" alt=\"Getting a sense of scale for the Red Bull Rampage, photo by William Saunders, Jaxson Riddle dropping in\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14054122/Red-Bull-Rampage-for-Scale_photo-by-William-Saunders_Jaxson-Riddle-dropping-in.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14054122/Red-Bull-Rampage-for-Scale_photo-by-William-Saunders_Jaxson-Riddle-dropping-in-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14054122/Red-Bull-Rampage-for-Scale_photo-by-William-Saunders_Jaxson-Riddle-dropping-in-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14054122/Red-Bull-Rampage-for-Scale_photo-by-William-Saunders_Jaxson-Riddle-dropping-in-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14054122/Red-Bull-Rampage-for-Scale_photo-by-William-Saunders_Jaxson-Riddle-dropping-in-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14054122/Red-Bull-Rampage-for-Scale_photo-by-William-Saunders_Jaxson-Riddle-dropping-in-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-274812\">all c. Red Bull, photo by William Saunders</p></div><p>And those drop-in chutes at 65-85° not only look steep, they’re close to vertical, and are only rideable with a good run-out at the bottom. It’s pretty wild, when you think about it in context.</p><div id=\"attachment_274820\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060247/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Long-Nguyen_Tom-Van-Steenbergen-testing-lines.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-274820\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060247/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Long-Nguyen_Tom-Van-Steenbergen-testing-lines.jpg\" alt=\"2021 Red Bull Rampage, photo by Long Nguyen, Tom Van Steenbergen\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060247/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Long-Nguyen_Tom-Van-Steenbergen-testing-lines.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060247/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Long-Nguyen_Tom-Van-Steenbergen-testing-lines-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060247/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Long-Nguyen_Tom-Van-Steenbergen-testing-lines-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060247/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Long-Nguyen_Tom-Van-Steenbergen-testing-lines-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060247/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Long-Nguyen_Tom-Van-Steenbergen-testing-lines-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060247/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Long-Nguyen_Tom-Van-Steenbergen-testing-lines-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-274820\">Tom Van Steenbergen, photo by Long Nguyen</p></div><p>Actually, Rampage is pretty wild any way you think about it!</p><h3>2021 Red Bull Rampage: How to watch?</h3><div id=\"attachment_274818\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060238/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Bartek-Wolinski_Szymon-Godziek-testing-lines.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-274818\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060238/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Bartek-Wolinski_Szymon-Godziek-testing-lines.jpg\" alt=\"2021 Red Bull Rampage, photo by Bartek Wolinski, Szymon Godziek\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060238/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Bartek-Wolinski_Szymon-Godziek-testing-lines.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060238/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Bartek-Wolinski_Szymon-Godziek-testing-lines-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060238/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Bartek-Wolinski_Szymon-Godziek-testing-lines-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060238/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Bartek-Wolinski_Szymon-Godziek-testing-lines-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060238/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Bartek-Wolinski_Szymon-Godziek-testing-lines-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060238/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Bartek-Wolinski_Szymon-Godziek-testing-lines-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-274818\">Szymon Godziek, photo by Bartek Wolinski</p></div><p>Here’s the deal, it’s the 20th anniversary of the first Rampage this year. With this actually being the 15th edition. So, 15 of the world’s best and craziest freeriders are out in southern Utah right now, getting ready to compete to see who has the best flow, the best tricks, and maybe the least sense of self-preservation.</p><div id=\"attachment_274819\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060243/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Long-Nguyen_Kurt-Sorge-testing-lines.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-274819\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060243/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Long-Nguyen_Kurt-Sorge-testing-lines.jpg\" alt=\"2021 Red Bull Rampage, photo by Long Nguyen, Kurt Sorge\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060243/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Long-Nguyen_Kurt-Sorge-testing-lines.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060243/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Long-Nguyen_Kurt-Sorge-testing-lines-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060243/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Long-Nguyen_Kurt-Sorge-testing-lines-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060243/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Long-Nguyen_Kurt-Sorge-testing-lines-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060243/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Long-Nguyen_Kurt-Sorge-testing-lines-768x461.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/14060243/2021-Red-Bull-Rampage_photo-by-Long-Nguyen_Kurt-Sorge-testing-lines-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-274819\">Kurt Sorge, photo by Long Nguyen</p></div><p>Some already snuck a peak over a month ago at the landscape that is being used for this year’s Rampage. And now, for the past two weeks, the riders and their support teams have been up in the Virgin, UT desert previewing the cliffs and planning their lines.</p><p>(<em>These three photos above were shot yesterday, Oct 13, as the riders were getting into the Rampage groove.)</em></p><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Bgfgvabq484?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></p><p>So, a couple of weeks of digging out new lines is about to come to fruition.</p><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/rMs_oncCL7c?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></p><p>Now they are training, dialing in those new lines, and practicing their planned tricks &amp; transitions.</p><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/KqBQfNeW23g?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></p><p>The real competition kicks off tomorrow, Friday the 15th of October at 11 am mountain time in Utah, and will be broadcast live on Red Bull TV. (That’s 1 pm on the east coast of the US,&nbsp; or 7:30 pm in Europe.)</p><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/yVBJyemu9hc?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;start=16&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></p><p>Watch it all go down live tomorrow, or burn a good part of your workday today reading up on Red Bull’s detailed Rampage coverage – past &amp; present – with videos, long-travel bike checks, and commentary from riders there and one’s who know better.</p><p><em><a href=\"https://www.redbull.com/int-en/events/rampage\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">RedBull.com</a></em></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"5a20e93224bc086e13dff2bca40c881f311be4fdaebdd8564e0011e43d901a71","category":"Cycling"}